<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="TI6" checkit-title="Partial fractions">
    <statement>
        
        <p>
            Consider the partial fraction decomposition <me> \frac{4 \, {\left(x^{2} - x - 3\right)}}{x^{3} + 4 \, x^{2} + x + 4}=-\frac{4}{x^{2} + 1} + \frac{4}{x + 4}.</me>  Use this decomposition to compute <m>\displaystyle\int \frac{4 \, {\left(x^{2} - x - 3\right)}}{x^{3} + 4 \, x^{2} + x + 4}dx</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <me>\displaystyle\int \frac{4 \, {\left(x^{2} - x - 3\right)}}{x^{3} + 4 \, x^{2} + x + 4}dx=\displaystyle\int -\frac{4}{x^{2} + 1} + \frac{4}{x + 4}dx=-4 \, \arctan\left(x\right) + 4 \, \log\left(x + 4\right)+C.</me>
    </answer>
</exercise>
